					<description><![CDATA[It’s a new dayOne for whichI did not pay It’s new to meAnd new to youwhat will we seeand what will we do I do not knowWill I shrinkor will I growShrink in fearOr grow in knowledge Will I be better todayThan I was yesterdayOr&#160;<a class="read-more" href="https://llgt.cafe/new">&#8230;</a>]]></description>
										<content:encoded><![CDATA[
<p>It’s a new day<br>One for which<br>I did not pay</p>



<p>It’s new to me<br>And new to you<br>what will we see<br>and what will we do</p>



<p>I do not know<br>Will I shrink<br>or will I grow<br>Shrink in fear<br>Or grow in knowledge</p>



<p>Will I be better today<br>Than I was yesterday<br>Or will I stay the same<br>Or grow in fame<br>Will I die to self<br>And learn to live<br>Will I keep<br>Or choose to give</p>



<p>Who knows<br>What the day will bring<br>Will it be different<br>Or the same<br>Is life a burden<br>Or is it a game<br>I give you my time<br>I sell it for a dime</p>



<p>Is it over now<br>Or just getting started<br>Will I glow bright<br>Or flame be retarded<br>Will I be a start<br>Shine from afar<br>Can you see my light</p>



<p>Can you see me fight<br>To resist myself<br>To lay in bed<br>And lay my head<br>And close my eyes<br>Or go instead</p>



<p>To go out<br>And change my world<br>To change myself<br>To be the same<br>Or build a shelf</p>



<p>To do something<br>For someone else<br>Of for myself<br>With someone else</p>



<p>To be alone<br>Or be with you<br>In mine own zoo</p>



<p>&nbsp;It is of the Lord&#8217;s mercies that we are not consumed, because his compassions fail not. They are new every morning: great is thy faithfulness. The Lord is my portion, saith my soul; therefore will I hope in him. Lamentations 3:22-24 (KJV)</p>
]]></content:encoded>
					
